Barely two days after some security officials were killed in Enugu State, another team of four policemen on stop-and-search duty on the outskirts of Enugu metropolis have been shot dead by armed hoodlums. The latest incident happened at about 3p.m. on Saturday at Obeagu community along Amaechi-Ekeotu-Agbani Town Road; leaving the road deserted till 7 p.m.   Fire destroys Osun market       Indian held over 134,700 bottles of codeine smuggled into…     ASUU keeps students, govt in suspense   Police spokesman Daniel Ndukwe confirmed the attack but did not give the number of casualties. Ndukwe said: “Police operatives have been duly deployed and are on the trail of the unknown armed assailants. You will be updated with further development, please,” he said. Some tricycle operators plying the road, who spoke on condition of anonymity, said that armed hoodlums came in a Sienna car and Lexus Sport Utility Vehicle (SUV) and opened fire on the unsuspecting policemen.   SPONSORED